messages.message:
My customer is on AI Hub ST - the Explore enterrprise button returns a 404. i’m guessing its due to them having their ‘upsell’ to commercial / enterprise user journies disabled because they are already sold :coolmoney:
Can we hide this carousel card for Ent customers?
This is a good catch - I think we should link to the pricing page instead @Weiming Wu
(I deleted the message I just sent, got confused from the other thread!) This might have to do with permissions - non-org admins can't see the billing page I assume, so we show them a 404.
Do we want to link to the pricing page for non-admin users? Maybe we should just still link to the blog post for non-admin users?
whats the blog post, sorry I didn’t see the full mesage
When you're logged out, you get taken to this blog post: https://instabase.com/blog/transform-document-heavy-processes-with-ai-hub-for-enterprise/
mmm I think from non-admin users that link doesn’t make sense either

I’d rather there was a link to “getting started” tutorial page, or Video on one of the carousel cards for logged in users.

@rachel.datlowe @Corey Brubaker @Brian
Better yet - Getting started card should appear for any new user, but be hidden once you’ve built something / created a chatbot

OR bonus point - let’s gamify it :trophy:  Have a card for each thing we want the customer to do as a new user:
• Converse with a doc - click here
• Create a chatbot - click here
• Publish an app - click here
like some products to do get you onboarded
For ST environments, we hide the Subscription page entirely. So this should just link to the pricing page ideally
Or we can hide the card entirely, but we need an odd number so would need to replace it with something!
Link to academy or Get started video!
